# AWS Services Used

### Amazon S3
Used to securely store and host the static website files, including HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and images.

### Amazon CloudFront
Acts as a Content Delivery Network (CDN), caching website content at edge locations around the world to improve performance and reduce latency.

### Amazon Route 53
Provides DNS management and routes traffic from the custom domain to the CloudFront distribution.

### AWS Certificate Manager (ACM)
Issues and manages free SSL/TLS certificates, enabling secure HTTPS communication.

### Origin Access Control (OAC)
Ensures that only CloudFront can access the S3 bucket, preventing direct public access to the website files.
